INSERT INTO `craft_matrixcontent_profile` (`id`, `elementId`, `locale`, `field_columns_column1`, `field_columns_column2`, `dateCreated`, `dateUpdated`, `uid`) VALUES
 ('1', '29', 'en_us', '<p>Catherine is the first and so far, the only woman to become chair and CEO of an Upstream E&amp;P Company in Nigeria. A graduate of  Ahmadu Bello University, Zaria, Catherine obtained a Diploma in Law and an LLB (Hons.) in 1985 and promptly called to the Nigerian Bar in 1986. She is a member of the Nigerian Bar Association, a fellow of the Institute of Arbitration and Conciliation, as well as a member of the Institute of Chartered Secretaries and Administrators.<br /></p>\n\n<p>Her career in the petroleum industry started when she joined Texaco’s Legal Department as Junior Counsel in 1987 and rose swiftly to become Company Secretary in 1997. In 2003, her Government and Public Affairs responsibilities were extended to Cameroon, Togo, Benin, Cote D’Ivoire, and the Democratic Republic of Congo. She joined Brittania-U Nigeria Limited in 2007 as Chair/CEO and has since steered the indigenous company to its current market leading position.</p>', '<p>Formerly on the Board of Directors of the Federal Ministry of Arts and Culture (2001-2002), Catherine’s leadership of Brittania-U has brought a number significant ‘firsts’. The Ajapa Floating Production Storage Unit, 100% owned and operated by the company, produced its first oil from drilling in 17 months; a feat yet to be equaled by any other company of its kind in Nigeria. She has set up six subsidiary companies in seven years, receiving numerous awards for good governance and management in Nigeria, the US, China, and Europe.</p>', '2016-06-03 06:31:29', '2016-06-03 09:02:29', '1f5aadd0-9a22-4f1c-871e-86cf49242c85'),
 ('2', '32', 'en_us', '<p>Currently the Chief Financial Officer at Brittania-U, Ahmed’s career found root at Schlumberger in Sedco Forex (A Schlumberger Drilling Company) in Oman as Manager Finance &amp; Administration from 1993 – 1996, after which he proceeded to Indonesia as the Division Controller from 1996 to 1998. He then went on to hold several positions as Controller and Finance Manager for Schlumberger Aberdeen (UK), Libya, Algeria, Saudi Arabia and Pakistan before moving to Iran in 2005. Prior to joining Schlumberger, Qazi had spent eight years in A. F. Ferguson amp;Co Chartered Accountants (PricewaterhouseCoopers- Pakistan) from 1979 to 1986 and then joined Shell Pakistan Limited (formerly Pakistan Burma Shell) as Assistant Chief Accountant from 1986 to 1993.</p>\n\n<p>He became the Group Finance Director of Nigeria &amp; Gulf of Guinea countries for Schlumberger in June 2011, after spending six years in Iran &amp; Kazakhstan as the Group Finance Controller, also serving as Financial Controller with Fortune 500 and high-tech companies.</p>', '<p> Ahmed holds a Bachelor’s degree in Commerce from the University of Karachi. He is also a Fellow of the Institute of Chartered Accountants of Pakistan (ICAP) and a Fellow Member of the Institute of Taxation Management of Pakistan. He has also undertaken business administration courses from Institute of Business Administration, Karachi and an advanced financial program from the Wharton School of Business, Pennsylvania. In addition, he was an active member of various social clubs at College level and was an active member of PEG( Pakistan Executive Group-Saudi Arabia).</p>', '2016-06-03 07:08:56', '2016-06-03 09:02:41', '17801fe3-0c2e-40c7-a92c-f81abd3a814f'),
 ('3', '34', 'en_us', '<p>Nwafor is the Manager, Exploration and Production. With over 16 years’ experience garnered from the Oil &amp; Gas industry in Nigeria and across the globe, Simon is an expert in managing risk complex projects (Hydrocarbon Assets), projects relating to reservoir studies, drilling, on site application supports which includes Seismic interpretation and Reservoir modeling, Coordination of geology &amp; Geophysics seismic interpretation unit, training of the new interpreters, report writing and presentations, Setting up of workstations unit and decision making relating to well proposal, drilling and completions.</p>', '<p>He started his career with a two-year stint at Nigeria Agip oil Company as a  geologist , after which he spent three years with Dege Conek Nigeria Limited (Oil &amp; Gas Service Provider) as a Senior Geologist and six years at AnKorPoinTe Integrated Limited, Subsidiary of HBT Consulting, Houston Texas(Oil &amp; Gas Services Provider) as  Manager Geology &amp; Geophysicist before joining Brittania-U as Manager, Exploration &amp; Production.</p>', '2016-06-03 07:10:01', '2016-06-03 09:02:51', '348a29cf-10e0-4c81-bc7a-119e99e05342'),
 ('4', '36', 'en_us', '<p>Julius is the manager of Brittania-U’s Warri Operations. A certified Public Accountant and a certified Information Systems Auditor, He graduated from New Jersey Institute of Technology with a BSc in Management Studies. He further took an MSc. in Accounting from Kean University, New Jersey, after being hired out of college by insurer State Farm as a Senior Insurance Auditor.</p>', '<p>He has worked in the United States for some of the biggest firms in banking, accounting, and insurance – State Farm, KPMG, Deloitte, and UBS. He has also provided advisory services to multi-national corporations, including SAS 70, Sarbanes-Oxley, and Integrated Audit covering IT General &amp; Application Controls for clients within the Financial Services &amp; Entertainment Industries.</p>', '2016-06-03 07:11:12', '2016-06-03 09:03:01', '951dbca0-c813-44a0-913d-7d8c68dc9700'),
 ('5', '38', 'en_us', '<p>Oluremi is the Manager for Compensation and benefits. A graduate of Ladoke Akintola University of Technology, Oyo State, with a Master of Business Administration (MBA) degree in Human Resources Management, Oluremi started her human resources management career with the defunct Midas Bank plc. in 2001. She later joined Network News 24 (NN24), before joining Brittania-U as compensation and benefits manager and later reassigned as Human Resources Manager.</p>', '<p>In addition to professional experience, she is a member of various local and international human resources bodies.</p>', '2016-06-03 07:13:59', '2016-06-03 09:03:11', 'fef86b5f-7149-4f4a-ba91-614ee3ab7fd1'),
 ('6', '40', 'en_us', '<p>Chibuzo is Supply Chain Manager for Procurement and Inventory, and he currently heads the Supply Chain &amp; Procurement unit at BUNL.<br /></p>\n\n<p>He started his career in 1998 as Procurement Officer with Eastern Bulkcem Company Ltd Port Harcourt. He then worked in 2 world class Projects in the Oil and Gas industry: Chevron Nigeria Agbami FPSO Project and Chevron Nigeria Escravos Gas to Liquid Project (EGTL). He joined Chevron Nigeria Agbami FPSO Project in 2007 and later was drafted into the SCM group of Chevron EGTL Project first as a Logistics Specialist and later as Materials De-Inventory coordinator until June 2014. He spent the last 9 years with Chevron Deep Water Agbami FPSO Project and Chevron Escravos Gas to Liquid Project (EGTL).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With about 18 years in Procurement and Logistics Management, he joined the BUNL team as Supply Chain Coordinator: Procurement &amp; Inventory in January 2015.</p>', '<p>He started consulting for Brittania-U on Supply chain management from October 2014 where he built an efficient workflow process to coordinate and manage Procurement; tracking materials movement / usage and maintaining adequate inventory management and control across locations. Very passionate about meeting and exceeding expectations, his dedication and very extensive knowledge of the industry has resulted in the improved performance of BUNL supply chain, creating net value, building a very competitive infrastructure and measuring performance globally.</p>\n\n<p>A member of American Production and Inventory Control Society – APICS, Chartered Institute of Purchasing and Supply – CIPS and Associate Member, Nigeria Institute of Management, he wields extensive experience in Supply Chain Management, Procurement, Logistics solutions, Inventory management and Operations.</p>', '2016-06-03 07:15:33', '2016-06-03 09:03:23', '79dddbe1-380d-4455-b693-ddec00ee9ffc');



